%N A228869 Numbers k such that 2 * (1^k + 2^k + 3^k + ... + k^k) == 0 (mod k).
%C A228869 See A228870 for the numbers not in this sequence.
%C A228869 Union of A226872 and the positive odd integers (A005408).
%C A228869 Also, positive integers k such that (p-1) does not divide k for every odd prime p dividing k (cf. A124240). - _Max Alekseyev_, Sep 07 2013
%H A228869 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A228869/b228869.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a> (first 1000 terms from Vincenzo Librandi)
%p A228869 q:= n-> andmap(p-> irem(n, p-1)>0, {ifactors(n)[2][.., 1][]} minus {2}):
%p A228869 select(q, [$1..100])[];  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 08 2026
%t A228869 Select[Range[100], Mod[2*Sum[PowerMod[k, #, #], {k, #}], #] == 0 &]
%o A228869 (PARI) isok(n) = (2*sum(k=1, n, Mod(k,n)^n))%n==0; \\ _Bruce Nye_, Mar 08 2026
